gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Jazz 128, Spurs 109
gameRecap.excerpt: The Jazz snapped a five-game skid as they defeated the Spurs, 128-109. Lauri Markknanen led the Jazz with 26 points, seven assists, and four rebounds as Jordan Clarkson added 22 points and 10 assists. Devin Vassell (27 points, nine rebounds, five assists) and Victor Wembanyama (22 points, 10 rebounds, five blocks) led the Spurs in the loss. The Jazz move to 27-31 as the Spurs fall to 11-47.
